&lt;p&gt;At DBeaver, our team has a shared vision to integrate data into the routines and decision-making process of every individual. With a dedicated community of over 10 million active users worldwide who constantly inspire us, our open-source approach fuels innovation within.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, DBeaver is the leading provider of cross-platform enterprise data and database software and we’re seeking a Product Marketing Manager to join our team. You will bridge the gap between internal product and go-to-market teams by owning the strategy on how we communicate our products and features. You&#39;ll become the expert on what DBeaver does, who it&#39;s for, and how it stands apart from the competition.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; This role can be based remotely in the United States or Europe, or hybrid in our offices in Belgrade, Serbia, or Budapest, Hungary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand and define how we strategically talk about DBeaver’s existing and future products and features: what they do, who they’re for, and why they’re different.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate DBeaver’s technical details into clear, compelling narratives for different audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with engineering/product, marketing, sales, and customer success to ensure strong internal alignment and understanding of DBeaver’s value and differentiation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help sales and marketing teams improve campaigns, collateral, and external messaging through internal education and alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape the voice of DBeaver in the global data market by defining and championing product differentiation that resonates with millions of users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accelerate product adoption and customer success through strategic messaging that makes complex database technology accessible and valuable to diverse audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are open to two different types of candidates for this role:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technical user or engineer who is seeking to transition into a marketing career. In this case, you are someone who has:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with relational databases or database management tools - you know how they function, how users interact with databases, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writing skills - you&#39;re empathetic to the needs of different personas and can translate technical concepts for both technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve been looking for a role that uses your technical knowledge, but adds a creative writing or marketing component beyond coding every day.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If this is you, we encourage you to drop a few sentences into your application or cover letter on why you’ve been seeking this type of career transition!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marketing or Product Marketing pro. In this case, you are someone who has:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of product marketing experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience quickly onboarding and understanding feature-rich, developer tool software products; or previous experience marketing for database or databases management tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success with cross-team alignment, messaging, and enablement for supporting existing and future product/feature launches.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re empathetic to the needs of different personas and can translate technical concepts for both technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical mindset, comfortable interpreting product metrics or market data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus Skills: Famili

